All passengers, including 18 players, die in the accident.The Chipolopolo's captain, Kalusha Bwalya, who is not aboard the ill-fated flight puts his efforts to build a new team and make a professional federation becoming later the national team coach and president of the Football Association of Zambia. programme.title: Break Point: a Davis Cup Story
programme.desc: Led by Rafa Nadal, the Spanish team were this year’s favourite until they suffered a serious setback. The team’s number two player, Roberto Bautista, had to leave the competition for his hometown to be at his father´s side during the last hours of his life. Without Bautista, Nadal and Feliciano López heroically managed to lead the team into the final. But then came the news that thrilled tennis fans worldwide: Bautista is coming back to the competition after his father´s funeral, and he´s ready to play. United again, the members of the Spanish team fight for victory in the grand final, where something far beyond tennis is at stake.

programme.title: SEVE - Artist, Fighter, Legend

This is his story, from members of his inner circle, other sporting greats and from himself via newly unearthed material.

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 1
programme.desc: Joe De Sena – Spartan Founder and Team Leader welcomes the team to Japan where they must climb iconic Mt. Fuji. As their first challenge, they scale the Atago stairs, a Samurai-honored tradition with a kettlebell for company. If that’s not enough, De Sena makes them run around the famed Imperial Palace. However, this time around there is a surprise for them from Rakuten. What other surprises are around the corner?

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 2
programme.desc: The Spartans are all set to climb Mt.Fuji a challenge that not only requires physical prowess but tremendous mental strength. A Japanese monk helps the Spartans cleanse their minds by guiding them through the time-tested practice of taking on the full force of an icy-cold waterfall – an experience they will never forget. As they undertake their arduous climb, their egos and frayed nerves begin to get in the way of staying together as a team. The shared responsibility of lugging along a 45-kg accessory certainly does not help their cause. Will they come together before it’s too late?

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 3
programme.desc: While the team begins to come together as one, awareness dawns on how different their individual attitudes and confidence levels are. While one of them, realizes they cannot complete the task and prepares to descend, another questions if her pace is setting everyone back. Keeping her on and walking at her pace would mean sacrificing watching the prized sunrise at the summit. Are they ready to give up on that ? They are getting beaten down, but they must go on. Will they make it before sunrise?

programme.title: Everyday Spartans: Episode 4
programme.desc: A sea of clouds and a magical sunrise await the team at the summit. With the team’s belief in themselves and each other reinforced, they think about what it took to overcome their obstacles. The moment is especially poignant for one member who pays tribute to the memory of his late son and spends a quiet moment in remembrance of him. As each of them grapple with the emotions that overtake them on the summit, Joe De Sena reminds them that reaching the summit is not the end of their journey – its’s only the beginning. Where will the Spartan spirit take them next?

programme.title: The Secrets of La Roja – World Champions 2010

programme.desc: 1879, nine-year-old Maria Sautuola and her father, Marcelino, discover the first cave art and accomplished paintings of galloping bison. But Maria's mother, devout Conchita, is disturbed at the idea that prehistoric savages could have created such magnificent art. The Catholic Church sees this as an attack on Biblical truth. And Carthailac, the leading prehistorian, condemns Marcelino and his discovery as fakes. The family is thrown into crisis and the cave locked up. It takes all their love for each other to find a way through to redemption and recognition.

programme.title: The Face of Love
programme.desc: Five years after the death of her beloved husband Garrett (Ed Harris), Nikki (Annette Bening) meets Tom, a man who who looks exactly like her deceased husband. Not only does Tom possess the same physical characteristics, but he also shares Garrett's kindness, humour, and passion for art. Suddenly, a flood of old feelings rush back to Nikki: she's met the love of her life. Again.

programme.title: Life at These Speeds
programme.desc: We all have those memories. Indelible, perfect memories that make you glow with happiness. Like the way the sun shone off her hair the morning you met her or the sound of your best friend’s laughter after an inside joke or your coach’s inspiring speech or daydreaming with the love of your life about your future together. After a teenager's friends are killed in an accident, he finds running allows him to remember them perfectly. Running however also brings him notoriety. Soon he finds himself caught between keeping the past alive and making new memories in the present.

programme.title: Meek's Cutoff
programme.desc: The year is 1845, the earliest days of the Oregon Trail, and a wagon team of three families has hired the mountain man Stephen Meek to guide them over the Cascade Mountains. Claiming to know a short cut, Meek leads the group on an unmarked path across the high plain desert, only to become lost in the dry rock and sage. Over the coming days, the emigrants must face the scourges of hunger, thirst and their own lack of faith in each other’s instincts for survival. When a Native American wanderer crosses their path, the emigrants are torn between their trust in a guide who has proven himself unreliable and a man who has always been seen as the natural enemy.

programme.title: Last Days In The Desert
programme.desc: Suffused with mystery, and set against breath-taking landscapes, this bold and dramatic interpretation of the temptations of Christ explores Jesus’ confrontation with the devil in his last days fasting Judean desert. Finally contemplating a return to civilisation, and his imminent death, Jesus happens upon a troubled family dealing with a much more earthly problem: the young son being desperate to leave the familial home against his father’s wishes, in search of the big city. Amid this family struggle we see Jesus wrestling not only with Satan, but also with his own faith.

programme.title: Poppy Shakespeare
programme.desc: N has been a day patient at north London's Dorothy Fish day hospital for 13 years - her ambition is never to leave. Then she meets glamourous new patient Poppy Shakespeare, an ad agency receptionist convinced she's not mad.

programme.title: Witchville
programme.desc: In the Middle Ages, Erik and Jason seek out his compatriot Malachy and force him to return to his homeland. When they arrive, they find that Malachy's father, the King, is dead and their lands are completely devastated. Both seek revenge against the Evil Red Queen.

programme.title: Battle for Skyark
programme.desc: In the near future the earth has become desolate and dangerous. Now inhabited by by a mysterious race of creatures, humanity has been forced to find refuge in the Skyark, a man-made city in the sky. As the population grows, space becomes scarce and only the rich and powerful can stay, dumping the poor and orphaned of Skyark to the abandoned earth. Among them is one boy, Rags, the son of a fallen commander who is determined to save his fellow orphans and exiles. Together with his friends, he must battle through the ruins of old earth, fighting off the horde of alien monsters to return to Skyark and bring peace back to the people.

programme.title: Mortdecai
programme.desc: Juggling some angry Russians, the British Mi5, his impossibly leggy wife and an international terrorist, debonair art dealer and part time rogue Charlie Mortdecai (Johnny Depp) must traverse the globe armed only with his good looks and special charm in a race to recover a stolen painting rumored to contain the code to a lost bank account filled with Nazi gold.

programme.title: 16 Blocks
programme.desc: They chose the worst man for the job. They expected him to fail, but he wasn't about to let a witness be murdered on his watch. Personal demons put Jack (Bruce Willis - Die Hard, Anti-Life) a New York City cop at rock bottom. But when he's assigned to escort a petty criminal to testify before the grand jury, a violent turn of events means this down-and-out cop needs to pull it together to save not only the life of the witness but his own as they are hunted across the city. The clock is ticking in this exhilarating race against time. Will justice be served or will there be two more bodies to add to the crime toll of the city?

programme.title: Dark Minds
programme.desc: A twisted psychological thriller about a man haunted by his past. After Josh (Zachary Quinto – 'Star Trek') experiences a series of hallucinations involving his brother (Jon Hamm – 'Baby Driver'), he places himself in the care of a young therapist Emily (Jenny Slate – 'Obvious Child'). As Emily is forced to wade deeper and deeper into Josh’s psyche, she fights to discover the truth.
